- debian package
- send version in init packet
- confirm each N (~10) packets or after ~0.1 s
- log about change remote IP
- packet reordering
- forward tcp port like "ssh -R" or "ssh -L"
- send as batches (packet includes previous data, MSGTYPE_MDATA), including resend after timeout or nak
- crypt magic, generate nonce, check nonce
- process shutdown only from remote ip (not from new one)
- hide key from command line
- if IP changed, perform extra authentication using key2
- extra command-line options (mtu, window, timeout, init-timeout, resend-time, target-cmd, link-cmd, ssh-cmd, bind-remote-port)
- ipv6
- msquic: https://github.com/microsoft/msquic
